data.description: Welcome to Conshohocken (aka Conshy), and to 118 Maple Street! Close proximity to Downtown Conshohocken, Main Street Manayunk, Plymouth Meeting, King of Prussia, and Philadelphia. Walking distance to Fayette St, tons of dining + shopping, and lots of corporate/office/job opportunities. Well-cared-for, 3-story, straight-through rowhome in a fantastic suburban community, which comes with the following: family room; dining room; spacious eat-in kitchen; first floor half bathroom; full bathroom on 1st floor; 3 spacious bedrooms + 1 WFH bedroom on 2nd + 3rd floors; rear/covered deck; private rear yard with patio; and 1 car parking in the rear. The kitchen features plenty of cabinet space, stainless steel appliances, eat-in capacity, and an open/light-filled workspace. The floor plan includes hardwood floors + great natural light, as well as easy living/entertaining options, where you can enjoy Greater Philadelphia's four traditional seasons in the rear yard/patio or on the deck. You can choose to walk, drive, or use public transit on a daily basis all while being just blocks away from Conshohocken's Regional Rail Station (1/2 mile away), as well as Blackfish, Flanigan's Boathouse, The Great American Pub, Guppy's Good Times, & Nudy's Cafe. This ideal + convenient location also allows you to walk, run, and bike along the Schuylkill River Trail, just a short distance from your front door. There are also plenty of amazing golf courses/clubs (Gulph Mills Golf Club, Philadelphia Country Club, Green Valley Country Club, & Union League's Liberty Hill) and summer pools (Ply-Mar Swim & Tennis Club, Ardmore Ave Pool, & Flourtown Country Club Pool) to enhance your inner-suburban vibe. 118 Maple Street provides an idyllic, suburban lifestyle, with convenient access to Greater Philadelphia's fantastic restaurants, shops, recreation, and history!
